summary.p:
In accordance with a first aspect of the present invention there is provided a hiking support systems comprising:
a first sleeve portion having a pocket for receiving at least one resilient pad of predetermined stiffness;
wherein the sleeve portion, having the pad inserted, is adapted to be worn by a user for providing support to the user while hiking.

In accordance with a third aspect of the present invention there is provided a hiking support systems comprising:
a first substantially planar panel adapted to releasably fasten opposite ends of the panel together to define a first sleeve portion; the panel including a pocket for receiving at least one resilient pad of predetermined stiffness;
wherein the sleeve portion, having the pad inserted, is adapted to be worn by a user for providing support to the user while hiking.
